"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-24-Chart-of-the-Day-Your-guide-to-the-Paris-2024-Olympics-1vuorxpr7Z6-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  Paris is embracing the Summer Olympics once again, promising an unforgettable experience a century after it last staged the Games. This will be the third time the French capital hosts the Olympics, following 1900 and 1924.  The city will welcome 10,500 athletes from over 200 national committees, including a refugee team. This edition marks a historic first, featuring an equal number of male and female athletes. A total of 329 medal events will take place, with 35 venues in Paris, the \\u00c3\\u008ele-de-France region, and across the rest of France.  Here's what you need to know about the Paris 2024 Olympics.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"